'''陈玉平'''（{{lang-en|Grace Lee Boggs}}, {{bd|1915年|6月27日|2015年|10月5日||}}）是一位美国华人作家、社会运动家和哲学家。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metrotimes.com/Blogs/archives/2015/10/05/grace-lee-boggs-dead-at-100|title=Grace Lee Boggs dead at 100|author=Michael Jackman|date=October 5, 2015|work=[[Metro_Times|Metro Times]]|access-date=October 5, 2015|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303181135/http://www.metrotimes.com/Blogs/archives/2015/10/05/grace-lee-boggs-dead-at-100|dead-url=no}}</ref>因1940年代至1950年代和[[塞利尔·莱昂内尔·罗伯特·詹姆斯|塞利尔·莱昂内尔·罗伯特·詹姆斯]]的政治运动为人熟知。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Aguirre Jr.|first1=Adalberto|first2=Shoon|last2=Lio|title=Spaces of Mobilization: The Asian American/Pacific Islander Struggle for Social Justice|journal=Social Justice|date=2008|volume=35|series=Asian American & Pacific Islander Population Struggles for Social Justice|issue=2|pages=1–17|jstor=29768485}}</ref>

==生平==
1915年出生于[[美国|美国]][[罗德岛州|罗德岛州]][[普罗维登斯|普罗维登斯]]一个华人家庭，父亲1911年从[[广东|广东]][[台山市|台山]]移民至[[美国|美国]]，在[[西雅图|西雅图]]经营餐馆，她1935年毕业于[[巴纳德学院|巴纳德学院]]，1940年获得[[布林莫尔学院|布林莫尔学院]]哲学博士学位，博士论文有关[[乔治·贺伯特·米德|乔治·贺伯特·米德]]。1953年搬到[[底特律|底特律]]，认识作家兼社会运动家[[詹姆斯·博格斯|詹姆斯·博格斯]]同年结婚。相濡以沫四十年直至丈夫1993年去世。两人毕生从事民权运动。<ref>Elaine Latzman Moon,[https://detroithistorical.org/shop/local-history-books/untold-tales-unsung-heroes-oral-history-detroit%E2%80%99s-african-american "Untold Tales, Unsung Heroes: An Oral History of Detroit's African American Community 1918–1967"] {{Wayback|url=https://detroithistorical.org/shop/local-history-books/untold-tales-unsung-heroes-oral-history-detroit%E2%80%99s-african-american |date=20160624042938 }}, Wayne State University Press, p. 156. Retrieved July 1, 2014.</ref><ref>[https://xw.qq.com/cmsid/20190627A0ACNU00 被奥巴马高度赞扬的美国华裔民权运动领袖陈玉平的一生]，腾讯新闻。</ref>

==著作==
*''George Herbert Mead: Philosopher of the Social Individual'' (New York : King's Crown Press, 1945)
*[https://www.marxists.org/archive/james-clr/works/1947/invading/ ''The Invading Socialist Society''] {{Wayback|url=https://www.marxists.org/archive/james-clr/works/1947/invading/ |date=20201109031324 }} (with C.L.R. James and Raya Dunayevskaya) (1947)
*''State Capitalism and World Revolution'' (with C. L. R. James and Raya Dunayevskaya) (1950).
*''Facing Reality'' (with C. L. R. James and Cornelius Castoriadis). (Detroit: Correspondence, 1958).
*''Revolution and Evolution in the Twentieth Century.'' (with James Boggs). (New York: Monthly Review Press, 1974).
*''Women and the Movement to Build a New America'' (Detroit: National Organization for an American Revolution, 1977).
*''Conversations in Maine: Exploring Our Nation's Future'' (with James Boggs, Freddy Paine and Lyman Paine). (Boston: [[South_End_Press|South End Press]], 1978).
*''[https://archive.org/details/livingforchangea0000bogg Living for Change: An Autobiography]'' (Minneapolis: University of Minnesota Press, 1998).
*[https://books.google.com/books?id=gQeeFbcOeqkC&printsec=frontcover ''The Next American Revolution: Sustainable Activism for the Twenty-First Century''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gQeeFbcOeqkC&printsec=frontcover |date=20200802191228 }} (with Scott Kurashige). (Los Angeles: University of California Press, 2011).

